-- AngloGold Approves Mponeng, Zaaiplaats Projects
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2012-02-15T09:10:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/anglogold-approves-mponeng-zaaiplaats-projects-correct-.html
(Corrects Mponeng project cost in lead.)  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  approved a
$416 million expansion project at its Mponeng mine in  South
Africa  and the Zaaiplaats phase-two project for $395 million.  These are low-risk projects at “cornerstone” mines,  Mark
Cutifani , the company’s chief executive officer, told investors
in Johannesburg today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  